"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-entertainment-2024-0810-1464333-snoop-dogg-opens-olympic-breakdancing\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Snoop Dogg officially opened the Olympic breakdancing competition to his hit songDrop It Like It's Hot.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 103, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 10, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Snoop Dogg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The American rapper, 52, and Olympic fan has been regularly spotted watching the Paris Games, and wore a full-dressage costume complete with breeches, a tailcoat, and hard hat when he watched the equestrian sport.\", \"from\": 105, \"to\": 318, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 109, \"end\": 117, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9997046703519349, \"rank\": 0.00022483413405236034, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 301, \"end\": 311, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"score\": 0.9999965301334387, \"rank\": 3.4638850140152433e-06, \"text\": \"equestrian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dogg, who is working for NBC throughout the Games, has also watched judo, beach volleyball and gymnastics, where he was seen sporting a T-shirt with Simone Biles' face on it.\", \"from\": 320, \"to\": 494, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 345, \"end\": 348, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.7393109486567446, \"rank\": 0.32293584652428103, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 469, \"end\": 481, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Biles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On Friday, he set down a brigadier, used in the theatre to mark the opening of a performance, ahead of the Breaking - the official name for breakdancing - at La Concorde.\", \"from\": 496, \"to\": 666, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dogg wore a red, white and blue tracksuit and black cap, while wearing a gold medallion in the same square where Marie Antoinette was sent to the guillotine two-and-a-quarter centuries ago.\", \"from\": 668, \"to\": 857, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 781, \"end\": 797, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.743295060285331e-20, \"text\": \"Marie Antoinette\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When he was carrying the Olympic torch ahead of the opening of the Games, he brought the bling with a world-shaped medallion and gold suit complete with a pocket watch.\", \"from\": 859, \"to\": 1027, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Los Angeles, the city he was born in, will host the 2028 Games, which currently do not have Breaking on the programme.\", \"from\": 1029, \"to\": 1147, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1029, \"end\": 1040, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999057783997, \"rank\": 7.938662765735226e-08, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dogg, whose real name is Calvin Broadus Jr, has had decades of hits includingWhat's My NameandYoung, Wild & Free.\", \"from\": 1149, \"to\": 1262, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1174, \"end\": 1188, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Calvin Broadus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Source: Press Association    \\u00a9 RT\\u00c9 2026.\", \"from\": 1264, \"to\": 1304, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"RT\\u00c9.ie is the website of Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann, Ireland's National Public Service Media.\", \"from\": 1305, \"to\": 1395, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1330, \"end\": 1353, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"score\": 0.9993664851268295, \"rank\": 0.0006339164685885233, \"text\": \"Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\"}, {\"begin\": 1355, \"end\": 1362, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999999787962681, \"rank\": 1.7004010015500774e-08, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"RT\\u00c9 is not responsible for the content of external internet sites.\", \"from\": 1396, \"to\": 1462, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1396, \"end\": 1399, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"score\": 0.9835396432123026, \"rank\": 0.013767790549921992, \"text\": \"RT\\u00c9\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/res